##-> Allows the firewall host to open connections to telnet servers on the 
##-> inside network. Telnet is very (!) unsecure. You should try not to use
##-> if it is not absolutely needed. Instead use SSH.
@IPCHAINS@ -A output -i @INTDEV@ -s @INTIP@ 1024:65535 -d @INTNET@ 23 -p tcp -j ACCEPT
@IPCHAINS@ -A input -i @INTDEV@ -s @INTNET@ 23 -d @INTIP@ 1024:65535 ! -y -p tcp -j ACCEPT
